-Bye.

24:12.285 --> 24:13.491
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

24:13.661 --> 24:14.867
ARLENE:
Yup, just up and left.

24:15.079 --> 24:17.491
Refused to tell me where he was going,
or what for.

24:17.707 --> 24:20.574
But I know it has something to do
with what happened in Iraq.

24:20.793 --> 24:23.455
-And he has never told you?
-No.

24:23.671 --> 24:26.754
That door is shut tighter
that bark on a tree.

24:26.966 --> 24:30.925
Girl, come to think of it,
every man I've ever dated or married...

24:31.137 --> 24:34.129
...has had some sort of secret
big ball of pain...

24:34.349 --> 24:38.843
-...that they keep all to themselves.
-Honey, that is every man, period.

24:39.062 --> 24:41.553
You know how they are.
Well, hey, Sookie.

24:41.773 --> 24:44.981
Not only do l have the worst hangover
I've ever had...

24:45.193 --> 24:47.935
...and feel like I could fall over,
I just took an order...

24:48.154 --> 24:51.897
...from a man who could not
keep his eyes off my tits the entire time.

24:52.116 --> 24:54.402
And his wife and two daughters
were at the table.

24:54.619 --> 24:58.157
-Men are just dogs.
-Dogs you cannot depend on for nothing.

24:58.373 --> 25:02.286
No matter how good they've been to you
or how different you thought this one was.

25:02.502 --> 25:05.665
-Except for Andy.
-Except for Andy. For now.

25:05.880 --> 25:06.995
Shut up.

25:07.215 --> 25:10.628
Can depend on them for one thing.

25:13.638 --> 25:18.553
Trouble. Insane, dangerous,
never-ending trouble.

25:18.768 --> 25:20.929
Way more trouble than they're worth.

25:21.145 --> 25:23.807
-Speaking of trouble.
-Sook.

25:24.023 --> 25:25.934
Hey, we need to talk.

25:26.150 --> 25:29.768
Are you out of your mind?
Mama and Daddy died in a flood.

25:32.448 --> 25:35.110
...Mack and Denise Rattray's trailer
got hit by a tornado?

25:35.326 --> 25:37.988
Vampires are pretty good
at covering their tracks.

25:38.204 --> 25:39.740
-What made you--?
-Hadley told me.

25:39.956 --> 25:43.323
You saw Hadley? Where?
How is she? How's Hunter?

25:43.543 --> 25:46.410
Yeah, they're fine. Hadley's working
at this...

25:46.629 --> 25:50.793
-...fairy night club that I went to.
-Fairy night club? Are you back on V?

25:51.008 --> 25:52.794
No. And I knew they was fairies...

25:53.010 --> 25:56.298
...because they blew me and Andy out
with light bombs from their hands.

25:56.514 --> 25:58.505
-Hadley told me they were.
-Hunter's there?

25:58.725 --> 26:00.841
-That's what she said.
-We gotta get them out.

26:01.060 --> 26:02.561
Can you take me there?

26:02.770 --> 26:07.434
Well, I think it's in this big field
out by old Thibodeaux farm...

26:07.650 --> 26:09.151
...but it ain't really there.

26:09.360 --> 26:12.193
Whatever. Fairies are bad news.
They can mess you up bigtime.

26:12.405 --> 26:15.818
They can, like, kidnap your life,
let alone how butt ugly they are.

26:16.033 --> 26:17.068
Right.

26:17.285 --> 26:19.367
A hate crime? Are you serious?

26:19.579 --> 26:22.742
The only four shifters I know of
in the entire Shreveport area...

26:22.957 --> 26:25.824
...have all been shot
in the last 24 hours.

26:26.043 --> 26:28.420
Somebody yells out, "Humans rule."

26:28.629 --> 26:31.462
-They're firing wooden bullets.
-Which are meant for vampires.

26:31.674 --> 26:33.790
Maybe they think they're good
for all supes.

26:34.010 --> 26:35.841
Thing is,
I can help you track them down.

26:36.053 --> 26:38.590
Sam, you ain't had the proper
investigative training.

26:38.806 --> 26:43.470
I can smell where somebody's been,
if they fired a gun. I can smell fear.

26:44.187 --> 26:46.018
I can shift into anything I need to...

26:46.230 --> 26:48.846
...and give you the most heightened
senses on the planet.

26:53.196 --> 26:54.982
I can get into places a human can't.

26:56.491 --> 26:59.403
Plus, I got a personal stake in this.

27:00.077 --> 27:02.204
I can't condone vigilante justice.

27:02.413 --> 27:04.074
Fuck you, Andy.

27:04.290 --> 27:06.747
You're human.
You got no idea what it's like...

27:06.959 --> 27:09.792
...having people wanna kill you
just because of what you are.

27:10.004 --> 27:13.838
Let me help you find these motherfuckers,
or I'll do it on my own. Your call.

27:17.220 --> 27:20.132
RIKKI: God, he is such a fucking parody
of himself.

27:20.348 --> 27:21.758
I hate him.

27:25.478 --> 27:28.345
[ALL SNIFFING]

27:30.066 --> 27:31.931
MAN 1: Check this shit out.
MAN 2: You're kidding me.

27:32.151 --> 27:34.733
MAN 1: Fucker killed Marcus.
MAN 2: He's got no right.

27:35.112 --> 27:36.238
JD.

27:36.447 --> 27:39.359
What the fuck you doing here?
You ain't a member of this pack.

27:39.575 --> 27:41.111
Well, I don't remember resigning.

27:41.327 --> 27:42.487
Yeah?

27:42.703 --> 27:45.194
Well, you gonna remember
me kicking your sorry ass out.

27:45.414 --> 27:47.826
MAN 1: Goddamn right.
MAN 2: You know it.

27:48.626 --> 27:50.992
Nice. Martha know about her?

27:51.212 --> 27:54.454
Don't you worry about me and Martha.
We got an arrangement.

27:54.924 --> 27:58.633
That include you sucking down
vampire blood like it's mother's milk?

28:01.180 --> 28:02.716
You out of your fucking mind?

28:02.932 --> 28:05.765
You gonna get yourself killed.
Not that I give a shit...

28:05.977 --> 28:08.343
...but you're gonna take down
these wolves with you.

28:08.563 --> 28:11.145
-Like you did Nate and Woody already.
-Listen...

28:11.357 --> 28:16.067
...if you wanna continue what we started
last night, I'll be happy to oblige.

28:16.946 --> 28:19.653
I accept the role of master of this pack.

28:21.284 --> 28:23.195
Now, you hold on.

28:23.411 --> 28:25.868
You passed up that opportunity
when you had the shot.

28:26.080 --> 28:27.286
WOMAN: That's right.
MAN 3: Yeah.

28:27.498 --> 28:29.705
-We got a new packmaster now.
MAN 2: Yeah.

28:29.917 --> 28:31.703
Let me guess. You.

28:32.712 --> 28:33.792
Me.

28:34.005 --> 28:35.461
And just how did that happen?

28:35.673 --> 28:37.834
Well, ain't nobody challenge me.

28:38.050 --> 28:39.915
Then let me be the first.

28:40.136 --> 28:41.842
And I know you'rejuicing.

28:42.054 --> 28:45.342
I'll be damned before I let you take down
my pack without a fight.

28:45.558 --> 28:47.799
MAN 1:
Gonna let him talk to you like that?

28:49.228 --> 28:52.015
-Yeah? Where's your second?
MAN 2: Right.

28:52.231 --> 28:54.938
Gotta have a second
before you can challenge the master.

28:55.151 --> 28:57.392
-That's the fucking law.
MAN 2: There you go.

28:57.612 --> 29:01.070
Unless you think you're above our laws.
Is that it?

29:01.282 --> 29:02.772
WOMAN: Of course it is.
MAN 2: Yeah, he does.

29:02.992 --> 29:06.234
Is this really the kind of guy
you want to be your packmaster?

29:07.705 --> 29:09.912
MAN 2: Hell, no.
RIKKI: Fuck, yeah.

29:10.458 --> 29:12.073
Yeah.

29:13.711 --> 29:15.292
Yeah?

29:15.504 --> 29:18.041
Well, which one of you's willing
to be his second?

29:19.175 --> 29:20.381
Huh?

29:20.593 --> 29:23.209
Put your fucking meat
where your bark is.

29:23.429 --> 29:25.090
|wi||.

29:29.101 --> 29:32.013
Well, I guess I should have
seen this coming.

29:32.480 --> 29:35.187
Because you're way too pretty
to not be stupid.

29:35.399 --> 29:36.479
Yeah?

29:36.692 --> 29:38.683
What's your excuse?

29:38.903 --> 29:40.894
[PACK MEMBERS CHUCKLING]

29:41.405 --> 29:43.441
WOMAN: Mouthy.
MAN 2: Yeah.

29:43.658 --> 29:45.990
You wanna punish me, Herveaux?

29:46.535 --> 29:48.400
Well, I'll be happy to give it to you.

29:48.996 --> 29:50.202
Just say when.

29:55.711 --> 29:57.576
MAN 1:
Get the fuck out of here.

29:58.047 --> 29:59.378
Back him up.

29:59.548 --> 30:01.379
[PACK MEMBERS
CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

30:15.022 --> 30:16.933
No welcoming party?

30:17.692 --> 30:21.526
-Can't be good.
-At least there's not a firing squad.

30:28.536 --> 30:30.527
DIETER: Congratulations, boys.
ROSALYN: There are the boys.

30:30.746 --> 30:32.782
KIBWE:
Congratulations. Heh, heh.

30:34.333 --> 30:36.540
Hail the conquering heroes.

30:36.711 --> 30:38.622
[JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

30:40.631 --> 30:42.246
Roman is very impressed.

30:42.925 --> 30:44.665
Please.

30:47.346 --> 30:49.962
And you don't need these anymore.

30:50.182 --> 30:55.973
Our heartfelt congratulations
and gratitude to you both.

30:56.188 --> 30:57.519
MOLLY:
Okay, stand still.

30:57.732 --> 31:00.098
Don't wanna accidentally
activate this thing.

31:00.317 --> 31:02.057
Wouldn't that be ironic?

31:02.278 --> 31:04.314
-But funny.
ROSALYN: Ha-ha-ha.

31:04.864 --> 31:08.527
I still can't believe you snagged
that little psychopath alive.

31:08.743 --> 31:10.699
You boys have certainly won me over.

31:10.911 --> 31:13.903
Have we learned who released Russell
from the ground to begin with?

31:14.123 --> 31:17.035
Salome has been interrogating Russell,
but....

31:17.251 --> 31:19.993
Well, he's been a little tight-lipped.

31:20.212 --> 31:21.748
We should know soon.

31:21.964 --> 31:25.627
But for a moment at least,
let's celebrate.

31:27.094 --> 31:30.177
Would it be possible for me to speak
to Chancellor Gainsborough?

31:31.015 --> 31:33.176
Chancellor Gainsborough
has revealed...

31:33.392 --> 31:36.304
...her true Sanguinist leanings
while you were gone.

31:42.026 --> 31:46.065
Anyway, I should go back
to interrogating Mr. Edgington...

31:46.280 --> 31:51.070
...who I'm hoping will provide us
with a wealth of useful intelligence.

31:52.244 --> 31:53.529
Be careful.

31:53.746 --> 31:55.577
He's the strongest vampire
I've ever met.

31:55.790 --> 31:58.748
Well, he's been silvered intravenously.

31:58.959 --> 32:01.336
He's quite impaired. Trust me.

32:01.545 --> 32:04.833
Congratulations again,
and thank you both for all you've done.

32:06.175 --> 32:07.460
We will not forget.

32:07.676 --> 32:08.802
It was our duty.

32:14.892 --> 32:16.974
-Boy Scout.
-Delinquent.

32:17.186 --> 32:18.221
[CHUCKLING]

32:18.771 --> 32:20.853
My boys. My boys.

32:21.065 --> 32:22.555
There are my boys.

32:22.775 --> 32:25.391
From here on out, officially known as...

32:25.611 --> 32:28.648
...the guys who took down
Russell Edgington.

32:28.864 --> 32:31.446
How's that sound?
Well done. Well done.

32:31.659 --> 32:35.243
Roman, that looks like a very special
bottle of blood.

32:35.454 --> 32:39.697
Why, yes it is, Rosalyn.
Eighteenth century Austrian hemophiliac.

32:39.917 --> 32:43.205
Not that I know too much
about these fancy antique bloods.

32:43.420 --> 32:47.663
All I know is it cost
a fucking fuck-load of money.

32:47.883 --> 32:50.135
Sit, sit.

32:55.808 --> 32:57.298
Interesting.

32:58.561 --> 33:00.893
You two have delivered...

33:03.065 --> 33:07.434
Probably the greatest individual threat
to vampire-human relations.

33:07.653 --> 33:13.444
And because of that,
you have saved many, many lives...

33:13.659 --> 33:18.528
...human as well as vampire,
so on behalf of them both...

33:19.248 --> 33:20.909
...I thank you.

33:21.125 --> 33:23.457
KIBWE: Cheers.
ROSALYN: Hear, hear.

33:23.669 --> 33:26.627
Well, in all fairness, Guardian,
we didn't really do anything...

33:26.839 --> 33:28.670
...except lead you to Russell.

33:28.883 --> 33:31.716
Oh, no, no, no.
You did exactly what I wanted.

33:32.970 --> 33:34.210
Now I know you're with me.

33:35.014 --> 33:37.926
You do believe in coexistence
with humans?

33:38.142 --> 33:39.427
Wholeheartedly.

33:43.647 --> 33:47.981
There are certain humans
I've felt protective towards...

33:48.777 --> 33:50.358
...in the past.

33:51.488 --> 33:56.778
Yeah, but you do believe that
the Sanguinista vision of morality...

33:56.994 --> 33:59.861
...endorses slavery, torture...

34:00.748 --> 34:06.334
...the rape of those who delivered us
into the life before death.

34:08.756 --> 34:09.791
Right?

34:11.926 --> 34:14.793
Well, I was never very religious...

34:15.012 --> 34:19.005
...but as long as the affairs of humans
do not personally impact me...

34:19.975 --> 34:23.342
...I do remain a pacifist.

34:27.191 --> 34:29.022
[LAUGHS]

34:30.444 --> 34:33.277
You are just too cool for school
to admit...

34:33.489 --> 34:35.980
...you believe in something
other than yourself.

34:36.325 --> 34:37.906
[LAUGHS]

34:38.077 --> 34:39.237
SALOME:
Excuse me.

34:39.453 --> 34:41.819
I should continue interrogating
our prisoner.

34:42.039 --> 34:44.872
Don't bother.
We're going to execute him.

34:45.084 --> 34:47.075
-But--
-We're at war.

34:47.294 --> 34:50.377
Just because we have caught
one very visible enemy...

34:50.589 --> 34:52.875
...does not mean that the war is over.

34:55.177 --> 35:01.093
I must admit I do find it ironic
that we proponents of coexistence...

35:01.308 --> 35:03.924
...find it so very difficult
to coexist with our enemies.

35:04.144 --> 35:07.011
But the reason for that is simple.

35:07.731 --> 35:08.766
They are evil...

35:10.192 --> 35:15.607
...cloaking themselves in Lilith to justify
their sadism, their greed, their lust.

35:16.073 --> 35:17.779
Lilith herself was not evil.

35:19.034 --> 35:20.319
Exigis 4:19:

35:20.536 --> 35:24.028
And blessed be the children of men...

35:24.248 --> 35:28.833
...for they are banished from the night
without end.

35:30.421 --> 35:33.379
They flame as sparks from a fire...

35:34.717 --> 35:35.957
...and last as long.

35:36.176 --> 35:39.509
But, Guardian, he knows so much.
And I agree, execution is warranted--

35:39.722 --> 35:42.759
Why would we believe anything
that he has to tell us?

35:43.517 --> 35:45.974
-And, oh, by the way, he is batshit crazy.
ROSALYN: Ha, ha.

35:46.729 --> 35:49.562
-Yes, Guardian.
-In fact, I want to execute him tonight.

35:50.399 --> 35:53.186
Soon as possible.
I wanna hit the links before sunrise.

35:53.402 --> 35:54.812
Has he been silvered?

35:55.029 --> 35:57.486
-Less than an hour ago.
-Mm-hm.

35:57.656 --> 36:00.693
Shall I give him another dose
and bring him to you?

36:00.909 --> 36:02.445
Excellent.

36:03.078 --> 36:06.491
And slap an iStake on him.
I don't wanna get dirty.

36:09.710 --> 36:13.999
Guardian, I request permission to visit
Chancellor Gainsborough in her cell.

36:15.883 --> 36:17.248
Why?

36:20.179 --> 36:21.339
She....

36:21.555 --> 36:22.840
She's my sister.

36:23.390 --> 36:25.176
ROSALYN:
Oh, my.

36:29.104 --> 36:31.481
You will be at the execution?

36:31.690 --> 36:33.066
Oh, I wouldn't miss it.

36:36.153 --> 36:37.359
And you?

36:37.946 --> 36:40.232
Oh, I love a good execution.

36:44.370 --> 36:46.486
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

36:55.756 --> 36:57.963
Holly said you were out here.

36:58.175 --> 37:01.884
Can't even come back to the service alley
to talk to me?

37:02.846 --> 37:05.007
I got some bad news, darling.

37:07.226 --> 37:09.091
Okay.

37:11.271 --> 37:12.602
Did you...

37:13.565 --> 37:17.103
...find whatever it was
y'all were looking for?

37:17.945 --> 37:23.110
Well, did you do whatever it was
you needed to do with it?

37:23.742 --> 37:26.779
Terry, I ain't Sookie.
I can't read your mind.

37:27.454 --> 37:32.323
Oh, baby. Whatever it is,
I wanna help you with it.

37:37.798 --> 37:38.913
I'm cursed.

37:41.677 --> 37:42.883
That ain't true.

37:43.095 --> 37:47.259
I got a curse put on me in Iraq.

37:48.308 --> 37:51.141
By a woman whose kids
somebody in my platoon shot one night...

37:51.353 --> 37:53.309
...when we was partying.

37:53.939 --> 37:57.852
Just trying to relax a little
in that fucking hellhole.

37:59.862 --> 38:01.898
Was the Fourth of July.

38:02.114 --> 38:05.527
Honey, there's no such thing as a curse.

38:05.742 --> 38:07.903
And even if there was,
why would she curse you?

38:08.120 --> 38:09.951
You didn't shoot her kid.

38:11.790 --> 38:14.372
Because I was aiming my gun
atherhead.

38:14.960 --> 38:17.326
And then I put three bullets in her.

38:18.672 --> 38:20.128
Oh, my God.

38:20.340 --> 38:22.126
Patrick told me to do it.

38:22.593 --> 38:25.380
-I knew it was wrong, and I did it anyway.
-Oh, my God.

38:25.596 --> 38:27.382
And now...

38:29.016 --> 38:31.257
...l'm being hunted
by an evil smoke monster...

38:31.477 --> 38:33.718
...that wants to kill me
and everyone I love.

38:34.563 --> 38:38.101
That's what set our house on fire,
not that ghost Mavis, like we all thought.

38:40.527 --> 38:42.643
I gotta go, baby.

38:43.238 --> 38:47.777
I gotta say goodbye to you
and Coby and Lisa.

38:48.035 --> 38:50.447
And Mikey.

38:50.662 --> 38:53.529
-Oh, Terry.
-I can't put y'all in danger.

38:56.877 --> 38:59.960
This ain't about my meds.
This is the worst thing I've ever done...

39:00.172 --> 39:03.335
-...and now it is time for me to pay for it.
-Now, you listen to me.

39:03.550 --> 39:05.962
I will help you through anything
life can dish out...

39:06.178 --> 39:08.510
...but I need you
to pull your end of things.

39:08.722 --> 39:12.010
I can't do anything
if you aren't staying on your meds.

39:12.684 --> 39:16.268
There's three little people
who depend on me to survive...

39:16.480 --> 39:20.098
...three little people
that I brought into this world.

39:20.734 --> 39:25.819
So I owe them,
and I need an adult to help me with that.

39:28.867 --> 39:31.700
Now, you wanna go back to Meadowglade
for a couple weeks...

39:31.912 --> 39:36.497
...get yourself straightened out,
get back on your medication, we can talk.

39:36.708 --> 39:38.539
-But--
-Arlene.

39:38.961 --> 39:41.748
If I stay with you, you will die.

39:42.172 --> 39:44.413
And so will the kids.

39:51.390 --> 39:53.221
Then you need to go.

39:58.188 --> 39:59.564
Thank you.

40:00.774 --> 40:03.561
Thank you for taking a chance on me.

40:04.861 --> 40:07.648
I wish it would have turned out better.

40:15.289 --> 40:16.825
Where is it?

40:16.999 --> 40:19.615
Uh.... Okay.

40:19.960 --> 40:22.326
Somewhere in this field.

40:22.546 --> 40:24.127
That's helpful.

40:24.339 --> 40:25.670
Well....

40:26.925 --> 40:28.961
[LAUGHTER]

40:29.219 --> 40:31.084
Over here.

40:33.515 --> 40:35.426
It's so freaking bizarre.

40:35.642 --> 40:41.512
It sounds like I'm right smack dab in
the middle of some sort of crazy nightclub.

40:42.441 --> 40:44.807
-But you're not.
-Fairies have cloaked it somehow...

40:45.027 --> 40:47.188
...or it's some other dimension
just next to us.

40:47.404 --> 40:49.486
I know it doesn't make a lick of sense,
but--

40:53.827 --> 40:54.862
Hey.

40:55.871 --> 40:57.657
Hey.

40:58.123 --> 41:01.741
That's my sister, you fairy fuckers.

41:02.169 --> 41:03.454
Bring her back here.

41:03.670 --> 41:05.501
SOOKIE:
Come on, Jason.

41:05.714 --> 41:08.000
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

41:15.891 --> 41:17.176
Hey.

41:17.392 --> 41:19.007
That's my fucking tie.

41:19.227 --> 41:20.558
Hey, dude.

41:20.771 --> 41:21.806
That's mine, man.

41:22.981 --> 41:25.393
I'll give you anything you want.
Let's go, come on.

41:26.360 --> 41:29.477
-You don't know what you're missing.
-lt's okay. You can keep it.

41:49.174 --> 41:50.289
SooHe?

41:50.509 --> 41:52.295
Hadley.

41:52.511 --> 41:54.752
Oh, my God. I thought you were dead.

41:54.971 --> 41:57.633
-l was sure the vampires got you.
-ls Hunter here?

41:57.849 --> 41:59.805
HADLEY: Of course.
SOOKIE: You gotta get him out of here.

42:05.315 --> 42:09.183
-These fairies are gonna try and take him.
-What? No. He's safe here.

42:09.403 --> 42:12.145
-They're keeping us both safe.
-They're not what they seem.

42:12.364 --> 42:13.695
Yes, but who is?

42:13.907 --> 42:15.647
SooHe.

42:16.410 --> 42:18.071
So good to see you again, Sookie.

42:18.286 --> 42:19.822
Uh, I don't think we've met.

42:20.038 --> 42:22.324
Yes, we have.
I helped you escape from Queen Mab.

42:23.041 --> 42:25.032
-Who?
-Claudine was my sister.

42:25.252 --> 42:28.585
